-- Nadal Plays Bolelli, Djokovic Faces Starace at French Open
-- B y   D a n i e l l e   R o s s i n g h
-- 2012-05-25T10:29:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-25/nadal-plays-bolelli-djokovic-faces-starace-at-french-open.html
Defending champion Rafael Nadal of
Spain will start his quest for a men’s record seventh  French
Open  title against Simone Bolelli of Italy.  World No. 1 Novak Djokovic of Serbia plays Italy’s Potito Starace, while 2009 champion Roger Federer of Switzerland faces
Tobias Kamke of Germany. Federer and Djokovic were drawn in the
same half. In Nadal’s half, Britain’s Andy Murray, ranked
fourth, starts against Tatsuma Ito of Japan.  In the women’s draw, world No. 1 Victoria Azarenka of
Belarus starts against Italy’s Alberta Brianti, while defending
champion Li Na of China plays Sorana Cirstea of Romania.
Russia’s  Maria Sharapova  was drawn against Alexandra Candantu,
also of Romania. Thirteen-time major champion Serena Williams of
the U.S., who was drawn in the same half as Sharapova, meets
 France ’s Virginie Razzano.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Danielle Rossingh at 
